By the way, we have gotten around this problem.  In one of the C++
classes I have some members that count iterations, etc. and declared
them as "unsigned int", being too smart for my own good it seems.
Apparently the compiler promoted them to long long int before trying
to wrap them.  Changing wrap(value) to wrap(int(value)) allowed us to
get it compiled.

